Global Fire Rated Expanding Foam Market Insights
Fire Rated Expanding Foam Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 1.9 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Fire Rated Expanding Foam Market Overview
The global Fire Rated Expanding Foam market is valued at approximately USD 2.5 billion in 2023 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 7.5% over the forecast period. This growth is driven by increasing construction activities, heightened awareness regarding fire safety, and stringent building codes demanding fire-resistant materials. Expanding foam is widely used for sealing joints, cracks, and gaps in buildings, particularly in fire-rated walls, ceilings, and floors. The adoption of fire-rated expanding foam in residential and commercial buildings is expected to contribute significantly to the market’s expansion, enhancing the demand for fire safety solutions in various industries globally.

